Load the data

ca_city_cases <- 
  read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datadesk/california-coronavirus-data/master/latimes-place-totals.csv")

bay_county_names <-
  c(
    "Alameda",
    "Contra Costa",
    "Marin",
    "Napa",
    "San Francisco",
    "San Mateo",
    "Santa Clara",
    "Solano",
    "Sonoma"
  )

bay_city_cases_no_smc <-
  ca_city_cases %>% 
  filter(county %in% bay_county_names) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(x))


# social distancing data
bay_sd <- readRDS("/Users/simonespeizer/pCloud Drive/Shared/SFBI/Restricted Data Library/Safegraph/covid19analysis/bay_socialdistancing_v2.rds") %>% 
  mutate(date = date_range_start %>%  substr(1,10) %>% as.Date())

# obtaining weekends
weekends <- bay_sd %>% 
  filter(!duplicated(date)) %>% 
  arrange(date) %>% 
  mutate(weekend = ifelse((date %>% as.numeric()) %% 7 %in% c(2,3), T, F)) %>% 
  dplyr::select(date,weekend)

bay_sd <- bay_sd %>% left_join(weekends)

Initial analysis - Bay Area (not including SMC) social distancing and case growth rate

bay_city_cases_no_smc_daily <- bay_city_cases_no_smc %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_cases_by_day = sum(confirmed_cases))

past_day_cases <- c(NA, bay_city_cases_no_smc_daily$total_cases_by_day[1:nrow(bay_city_cases_no_smc_daily)-1])

bay_city_cases_no_smc_daily <- bay_city_cases_no_smc_daily %>% 
  cbind(past_day_cases) %>% 
  mutate(growth_rate = total_cases_by_day / past_day_cases)

bay_sd_daily <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date >= min(bay_city_cases_no_smc_daily$date)) %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))

past_day_leaving_home <- c(NA, bay_sd_daily$percent_leaving_home[1:nrow(bay_sd_daily)-1])

bay_sd_daily <- bay_sd_daily %>% 
  cbind(past_day_leaving_home) %>%
  mutate(leaving_home_change = percent_leaving_home - past_day_leaving_home) %>%
  left_join(bay_city_cases_no_smc_daily)

bay_sd_daily %>% ggplot(
  aes(x = date)) +
    geom_line(aes(y = leaving_home_change, color="Leaving home")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = growth_rate, color = "Cases")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*1, name = "Daily case growth rate")) + 
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) +
  labs(y = "Change in percent of devices leaving home", x = "Date", color = "Data", title = "LA Times Case Data and Social Distancing")

NYT case data

opts_knit$set(root.dir = "/Users/simonespeizer/Documents/2020 Spring Quarter/CEE 218Z/covid-19-data")

setwd("/Users/simonespeizer/Documents/2020 Spring Quarter/CEE 218Z/covid-19-data")
covid_nyt_county <- read_csv("us-counties.csv")
covid_nyt_bay_daily <- covid_nyt_county %>% 
  filter(state == "California") %>% 
  filter(county %in% bay_county_names) %>% 
  group_by(date) %>% 
  summarize(total_cases_by_day = sum(cases)) %>%
  filter(total_cases_by_day >= 10)

past_day_cases_nyt <- c(NA, covid_nyt_bay_daily$total_cases_by_day[1:nrow(covid_nyt_bay_daily)-1])

covid_nyt_bay_daily <- covid_nyt_bay_daily %>% 
  cbind(past_day_cases_nyt) %>% 
  mutate(growth_rate = total_cases_by_day / past_day_cases_nyt)

bay_sd_daily_nyt_match <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date >= min(covid_nyt_bay_daily$date)) %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))

past_day_leaving_home_nyt <- c(NA, bay_sd_daily_nyt_match$percent_leaving_home[1:nrow(bay_sd_daily_nyt_match)-1])

bay_sd_daily_nyt_match <- bay_sd_daily_nyt_match %>% 
  cbind(past_day_leaving_home_nyt) %>%
  mutate(leaving_home_change = percent_leaving_home - past_day_leaving_home_nyt) %>%
  left_join(covid_nyt_bay_daily)

bay_sd_daily_nyt_match %>% ggplot(
  aes(x = date)) +
    geom_line(aes(y = leaving_home_change, color="Leaving home")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = growth_rate*10, color = "Cases")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*10, name = "Daily case growth rate")) + 
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) +
  labs(y = "Change in percent of devices leaving home", x = "Date", color = "Data", title = "NYT Case Data and Social Distancing")
